		 	<span id="comment_score_64211128" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64211128); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~sanf780">sanf780</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~sanf780">( 4055211 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64211128"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64211128">Be aware that routers/firewalls/access points tend to be powered on all the time. Appliances, even with firmware like openwrt, do tend to consume less power than whole computers. They also tend to be smaller - some people living in company care about aesthetics. No need to have indoors look like rooms from anime Serial Experiments Lain.
<p>Unfortunately, appliances tend to be slow. Features like Packet Inspection will impact routing throughput.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64211128">

</div>
