	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64211140">I ran a multi homed Linux or BSD box for decades as a firewall before wifi was a thing.  No reason you can't still do that of course.
<br> <br>
If you want wifi with advanced features like 4x4 (or 8x8!) MIMO you are probably better off with a dedicated wifi router running DD or OpenWRT.  Or you could use such a device as a simple access point behind your dedicated firewall box.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64211140">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64211140" class="btn link" href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23214388&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64211140" onclick="D2.replyTo(64211140); return false;">Reply to This</a> 	<a href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
	<div class="comment_share sharethis-0 hide"><span class="au"></span>
