<div id="comment_status_64211194" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64211194" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64211194" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64211194" name="comment_link_64211194" href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23214388&amp;cid=64211194" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64211194)" >Use added adapter for external side</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64211194" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64211194); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>3</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~laughingskeptic">laughingskeptic</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~laughingskeptic">( 1004414 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64211194">		
		on Saturday February 03, 2024 @03:18PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23214388&amp;cid=64211194">#64211194</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64211194">Many integrated Ethernet adapters support IPMI.  You do not want to expose that to the internet and can avoid doing so by using the integrated port on the internal side and the added adapter on the external side.  See for instance: <a href="https://www.shadowserver.org/what-we-do/network-reporting/open-ipmi-report/" title="shadowserver.org">https://www.shadowserver.org/w...</a> [shadowserver.org]</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64211194">
