		<div id="comment_body_64211288">I was looking at performing a similar project, and at this point I'm leaning towards pfSense for the software.  Regarding the hardware, there are a number of <a href="https://www.amazon.com/HUNSN-Firewall-Appliance-OPNsense-Celeron/dp/B0BP8ZCT8Y?source=ps-sl-shoppingads-lpcontext&amp;ref_=fplfs&amp;smid=A30LFBTK9XBZW2&amp;th=1" title="amazon.com">devices like this</a> [amazon.com] which should be pretty sufficient.  Since this is running a full x86_64 processor, it will probably be more power hungry than your traditional ARM-powered networking device.  For ARM-based options, a <a href="https://www.amazon.com/OpenSource-Wireless-Dual-Band-MediaTek-Bundle3-BPI/dp/B0BDG6R41Q/ref=asc_df_B0BDG6R41Q/?tag=hyprod-20&amp;linkCode=df0&amp;hvadid=658814150159&amp;hvpos=&amp;hvnetw=g&amp;hvrand=12262866645032451476&amp;hvpone=&amp;hvptwo=&amp;hvqmt=&amp;hvdev=c&amp;hvdvcmdl=&amp;hvlocint=&amp;hvlocphy=9003849&amp;hvtargid=pla-2064377604166&amp;mcid=ed4234132e2c3c56a9edf139942cfe0e&amp;th=1" title="amazon.com">Banana Pi like this</a> [amazon.com] might work, but your options might be limited to Linux (pfSense runs on FreeBSD).</div>
