			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64212064"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64212064"><p>I'm surprised no one has mentioned David Cinege's <i>Linux Router Project</i> yet (<a href="https://www.linuxjournal.com/article/3223" title="linuxjournal.com">LRP</a> [linuxjournal.com]), as it would be ideal for this task.</p><p>It fits on a single floppy and will run like a champ on any Pentium class machine with 12-16MB of RAM. If your mobo has PCI slots, I would splurge on a couple of 3c905-TX (one of WAN, one for LAN, rock solid 2.0.36 module) and you're all set! I even run the Junkbuster proxy on mine.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64212064">

